  "title": "Area Manager (F&B)",
  "description": "<p>Job description</p><p><strong>Job Scope/ Responsibilities For Area Manager</strong><br /></p><p><strong>1. Operational Oversight</strong></p><p>·         Supervise and support daily operations of multiple drink stalls across assigned outlets.</p><p>·         Ensure adherence to company SOPs, hygiene and NEA regulations, and food safety standards.<br /></p><p><strong>2. Staff Management, Monitoring & Disciplinary Action</strong></p><p>·         Lead, train, and motivate coffee shop supervisors and drink counter staff to maintain high performance and service quality.</p><p>·         Monitor staff attendance, punctuality, and on-the-job behaviour through regular site visits and spot checks.</p><p>·         Address misconduct or poor performance promptly : </p><p>          I.            Provide coaching or verbal counselling for minor issues.</p><p>          II.            Prepare and issue written warnings when required, following fair disciplinary procedures and MOM</p><p>guidelines.</p><p>·         Recommend further action (e.g., suspension or termination) for repeated or serious violations.</p><p>·         Maintain accurate records of staff incidents, warnings, and disciplinary actions.<br /></p><p><strong>3. Sales, Cost & Cash Management</strong></p><p>·         Monitor daily sales and implement strategies to achieve revenue and profitability targets.</p><p>·         Oversee proper cash-handling daily cash counts, bank deposits, and reconciliation of sales reports.</p><p>·         Investigate and resolve cash discrepancies promptly.</p><p>·         Control operating expenses, including manpower, inventory, and wastage.<br /></p><p><strong>4. Repair & Maintenance</strong></p><p>·         Inspect outlets for equipment, furniture, and facility issues.</p><p>·         Coordinate with vendors for timely repairs and servicing of machinery and fittings.<br /></p><p><strong>5. Quality & Customer Service</strong></p><p>·         Ensure consistent product quality and service standards across all outlets.</p><p>·         Handle customer feedback, resolve complaints, and drive service improvements.<br /></p><p><strong>6. Inventory & Supply Chain</strong></p><p>·         Oversee ordering and stock management for cigarettes.</p><p>·         Coordinate with suppliers for timely replenishment.<br /></p><p><strong>7. Reporting & Compliance</strong></p><p>·         Prepare operational, financial, and disciplinary reports for management review.</p><p>·         Ensure compliance with local regulations, including licensing and workplace safety.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements :</strong><br /></p><p>·         Passion for the F&B industry and its operational processes.</p><p>·         Diploma in F&B or related disciplines</p><p>·         Minimum 5 years of experience in food court or coffee shop operations.</p><p>·         Ability to foster positive working relationships.</p><p>·         Strong leadership qualities with excellent analytical and decision making.</p><p>·         Computer knowledge.</p><p>·         Preferably to process with own transport</p>",
